00:35:11.610 --> 00:35:17.430
Network Services are another piece of the
offering that we have in Mac OS X Server,

00:35:17.540 --> 00:35:21.050
and that includes some of the lower layer
networking capabilities that you use to

00:35:21.050 --> 00:35:23.570
set up a network and servers themselves.

00:35:23.700 --> 00:35:28.490
And these are things like DNS,
which are used for setting

00:35:28.680 --> 00:35:32.510
up domain name servers,
and of course there, as this is Unix,

00:35:32.510 --> 00:35:33.700
we're leveraging Bind.

00:35:33.700 --> 00:35:37.020
And we also have DHCP for
address assignment,

00:35:37.020 --> 00:35:40.700
as well as SLP,
which does dynamic name lookup.

00:35:40.700 --> 00:35:43.700
It's very similar to
AppleTalk's dynamic name lookup,

00:35:43.700 --> 00:35:48.580
but it's a protocol that was designed
specifically for TCP by a standards body.

00:35:48.700 --> 00:35:51.340
