00:37:41.920 --> 00:37:44.040
For those of you who aren't
familiar with Macintosh Manager,

00:37:44.040 --> 00:37:45.700
just a brief overview.

00:37:45.700 --> 00:37:48.320
Macintosh Manager is a product
that has a server component

00:37:48.320 --> 00:37:49.730
as well as a client component.

00:37:50.180 --> 00:37:55.400
It really provides what we like to think
of as two key pieces of functionality.

00:37:55.550 --> 00:37:58.830
We talk about the virtual desktop,
the ability to move

00:37:58.830 --> 00:38:00.540
preferences and bookmarks.

00:38:00.720 --> 00:38:04.420
Ken mentioned them some in the success
story where we have the ability to

00:38:04.420 --> 00:38:08.740
move things around to take advantage
of people going to different machines.

00:38:08.800 --> 00:38:11.680
It also provides a piece of
what we call resource policy,

00:38:11.680 --> 00:38:14.030
which restricts access
to certain resources as

00:38:14.380 --> 00:38:15.770
defined by the administrator.

00:38:15.770 --> 00:38:18.710
For example, whether or not people
can go to the chooser,

00:38:18.820 --> 00:38:20.800
what applications they can launch.

00:38:20.800 --> 00:38:24.690
So basically,
kind of configure the experience that

00:38:24.710 --> 00:38:27.800
the user has on their desktop machines.

00:38:27.800 --> 00:38:30.530
Network Assistant does
not require a server,

00:38:30.530 --> 00:38:33.590
but it is bundled as part of
the product because it is a

00:38:33.710 --> 00:38:35.800
very useful administrative tool.

00:38:35.800 --> 00:38:39.450
What Network Assistant does is
there's an administrative workstation

00:38:39.450 --> 00:38:41.080
as well as a client component.

00:38:41.080 --> 00:38:43.500
And again,
we can break Network Assistant down

00:38:43.500 --> 00:38:44.800
into two key pieces.

00:38:44.800 --> 00:38:46.870
One we like to think of as interaction.

00:38:46.870 --> 00:38:49.850
It gives you the ability to
communicate with the user either

00:38:49.920 --> 00:38:53.680
through text chatting or through
sharing screens or through controlling

00:38:53.790 --> 00:38:55.800
screens to large numbers of users.

00:38:55.800 --> 00:38:57.950
The second piece we like to
consider is an administrative

00:38:57.950 --> 00:39:00.330
maintenance component of the product,
which allows the user to

00:39:00.720 --> 00:39:02.800
configure workstations similar
to their own or to their own.

00:39:02.800 --> 00:39:02.800
So, this is a very useful tool.

00:39:02.800 --> 00:39:07.100
The third component, NetBoot,
is a tool to help make

00:39:07.100 --> 00:39:09.800
administrators' life easier,
basically around the

00:39:09.800 --> 00:39:09.800
management of the client OS.

00:39:09.800 --> 00:39:12.690
What we do is we provide a
server-based OS image that

00:39:12.900 --> 00:39:14.790
then remote clients can boot.

00:39:14.850 --> 00:39:17.800
So we have administration and management
of the OS in one central location.

00:39:17.800 --> 00:39:21.800
So, we have a server-based OS image
that then remote clients can boot.

00:39:21.800 --> 00:39:27.800
So, we have administration and management
of the OS in one central location.

00:39:29.810 --> 00:39:33.820
What I'd like to talk about are some
of the goals that we have for Macintosh

00:39:33.820 --> 00:39:35.540
Manager in the future releases.

00:39:35.670 --> 00:39:39.530
And I think primarily to our
efforts is simplification.

00:39:39.660 --> 00:39:43.350
What we found is there's a great
increase in the number of desktop

00:39:43.400 --> 00:39:46.590
machines without a corresponding
increase in administrators to

00:39:46.590 --> 00:39:48.000
manage and take care of those.

00:39:48.120 --> 00:39:51.030
So anything that we can do,
any work that we can do to simplify

00:39:51.060 --> 00:39:54.560
that experience and make it easier
for administrators to work with,

00:39:54.720 --> 00:39:57.210
we want to try to accomplish.

00:39:57.430 --> 00:39:59.800
Macintosh Manager has been very closed.

00:39:59.800 --> 00:40:02.260
We had our own proprietary database.

00:40:02.260 --> 00:40:03.680
We didn't give access
to the login screen.

00:40:03.680 --> 00:40:07.410
We need to work to make it more open
and more available for developers

00:40:07.770 --> 00:40:08.750
to interact with the products.

00:40:08.870 --> 00:40:15.020
We need to start moving
in that direction,

00:40:15.020 --> 00:40:15.020
and that's a goal of ours.

